               <msContents>
                  <summary>A selection of entries on nobles and statesmen (hence ‘Khizāna-yi Umarā’) culled from Āzād’s Khizāna-yi ‘Āmira.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_320-item1">
                     <author key="person_f1253">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">G̲h̲ulām ʻAlī Āzād Bilgrāmī, Sayyid, 1704-1786</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7292">Khizānah-ʼi ʻUmarā</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7292">خزانۀ امراء</title>
                     <note>The title ‘Khizāna-yi Umarā’ does not appear to be given in the text itself.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">آصف جاه غفران پناه جد مادری او ابو سعد الله خان وزیر اعظم صاحب قران ثانی پادشاه جهان است</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">خزانه و غله را هر قدر که توانستند فرستادند</explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon</colophon>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>See N. Bland, "On the Earliest Persian Biography of Poets, by Muhammad Aúfi, and on Some Other Works of the Class Called Tazkirat ul Shuârá." <title>The Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland</title>, Vol. 9 (1847), p. 150, n.1.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
